UNEXPLAINED DEATHS, DRUG ADDICTS - IRELAND (DUBLIN)
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Unexplained deaths, human - UK (Scotland) 20000511004948
Unexplained deaths, human - UK (Scotland) (09) 20000522204630
Date: 24 May, 2000, 17:15 GMT 18:15
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC

Eight heroin users have died in Dublin leading investigators to question
whether the cause of death is related to the cases that have occurred in
Glasgow, Scotland during the past two weeks. Anthrax has been ruled out in
the Glasgow cases. The investigation is continuing. Some officials are
calling for a Europe-wide alert.
